'''Wait But Why（WBW）'''是由蒂姆·厄本（Tim Urban）和安德鲁·芬恩（Andrew Finn）创建的[[網站|网站]]，发表厄本的文章。该网站以长篇博客的形式涵盖了一系列主题。<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Davis|first=Noah|date=30 October 2014|title=How Do You Make a Living, Email Newsletter Writer?|url=https://psmag.com/economics/make-living-email-newsletter-writer-93394|magazine=[[Pacific_Standard|Pacific Standard]]|access-date=22 December 2015|archive-date=2022-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220316131430/https://psmag.com/economics/make-living-email-newsletter-writer-93394}}</ref> 文章配上简略的插图，对各种主题进行深入讨论，包括[[人工智能|人工智能]]，[[外层空间|外太空]]和[[延宕|拖延症]]。<ref name="WBW & Politics">{{Cite web|title=Tech nerds are smart. But they can't seem to get their heads around politics|url=https://www.vox.com/2015/8/27/9214015/tech-nerds-politics|accessdate=4 September 2016|author=Roberts|date=27 August 2015|first=David|work=Vox|publisher=[[Vox_Media|Vox Media]]|archive-date=2022-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220410051424/https://www.vox.com/2015/8/27/9214015/tech-nerds-politics}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Grothaus|first=Michael|date=5 March 2015|title=The Secrets Of Writing Smart, Long-form Articles That Go Absolutely Viral|url=https://www.fastcompany.com/3042312/most-creative-people/the-secrets-of-writing-smart-longform-articles-that-go-absolutely-viral|magazine=[[Fast_Company_(magazine)|Fast Company]]|access-date=22 December 2015|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222161935/https://www.fastcompany.com/3042312/most-creative-people/the-secrets-of-writing-smart-longform-articles-that-go-absolutely-viral}}</ref>

== 历史 ==
网站早期，博客内容聚焦于[[社会化媒体|社交媒体]]和对技术的有趣讽刺，例如《在Facebook上讨人烦的七招》<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://waitbutwhy.com/2013/07/7-ways-to-be-insufferable-on-facebook.html|title=7 Ways to Be Insufferable on Facebook - Wait But Why|date=2013-07-08|work=Wait But Why|accessdate=2018-03-20|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517025315/https://waitbutwhy.com/2013/07/7-ways-to-be-insufferable-on-facebook.html}}</ref> 和《关于电子邮件的11个尴尬之处》，<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://waitbutwhy.com/2013/12/11-awkward-things-about-email.html|title=11 Awkward Things About Email - Wait But Why|date=2013-12-04|work=Wait But Why|accessdate=2018-03-20|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220408011350/https://waitbutwhy.com/2013/12/11-awkward-things-about-email.html}}</ref> 后来厄本转向更加深刻的主题。 2014年5月21日，厄本发布了《费米悖论》一文，广受欢迎。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://waitbutwhy.com/2014/05/fermi-paradox.html|title=The Fermi Paradox - Wait But Why|date=2014-05-21|work=Wait But Why|accessdate=2018-03-20|language=en-US|archive-date=2022-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220514032300/https://waitbutwhy.com/2014/05/fermi-paradox.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title="We’re in the climax of a movie": Tim Urban on humanity’s wild future|url=https://www.vox.com/podcasts/2020/2/10/21131219/tim-urban-wait-but-why-ezra-klein-show-future-of-humanity-technology-ai-climate-change|accessdate=2020-04-25|author=Klein|date=2020-02-10|first=Ezra|work=Vox|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109043540/https://www.vox.com/podcasts/2020/2/10/21131219/tim-urban-wait-but-why-ezra-klein-show-future-of-humanity-technology-ai-climate-change}}</ref>

该网站最初的口号是“每周一和周四更新”。随着帖子长度的增加和内容变得更加详细，自2015年起口号先是改成“每周二更新”，接着是“大概每周二更新”，后来成为“偶尔更新”。<ref name="Trying Something Different With the Schedule">{{Cite news|author=Urban|first=Tim|title=Trying Something Different With the Schedule|url=http://waitbutwhy.com/2015/03/trying-something-different-schedule.html|accessdate=23 June 2017|date=3 March 2015|publisher=Wait But Why|archive-date=2021-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023090440/https://waitbutwhy.com/2015/03/trying-something-different-schedule.html}}</ref>

因为对科学和技术的讨论，''Wait But Why'' 引起了[[伊隆·马斯克|伊隆·马斯克]]的注意，作者得以完成了一系列关于马斯克的文章。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Elon Musk: The World's Raddest Man|url=https://waitbutwhy.com/2015/05/elon-musk-the-worlds-raddest-man.html|date=2015-05-07|access-date=2020-12-31|archive-date=2022-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517194620/https://waitbutwhy.com/2015/05/elon-musk-the-worlds-raddest-man.html}}</ref> 2015年6月，伊隆·马斯克询问厄本是否愿意撰写介绍自己的公司及其周边行业的文章，<ref name="World's Raddest Man">{{Cite news|author=Urban|first=Tim|title=Elon Musk: The World's Raddest Man|url=http://waitbutwhy.com/2015/05/elon-musk-the-worlds-raddest-man.html|accessdate=10 March 2016|date=7 May 2015|publisher=Wait But Why|archive-date=2016-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307004340/http://waitbutwhy.com/2015/05/elon-musk-the-worlds-raddest-man.html}}</ref> 于是厄本多次采访马斯克，两人讨论了[[可持续交通系统|可持续交通]]， [[太阳能|太阳能]]，<ref>{{Cite web|title=Elon Musk just made an incredibly important point about solar energy|url=http://www.businessinsider.com.au/elon-musk-just-made-an-incredibly-important-point-about-solar-energy-2015-12|accessdate=22 December 2015|author=Harrington|date=16 December 2015|first=Rebecca|work=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]]|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222120236/http://www.businessinsider.com.au/elon-musk-just-made-an-incredibly-important-point-about-solar-energy-2015-12}}</ref><ref name="UtahSolar">{{Cite news|author=Chow|first=Lorraine|title=Elon Musk: We Can Power America by Covering Small Corner of Utah With Solar|url=https://ecowatch.com/2015/12/17/elon-musk-solar/|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=17 December 2015|publisher=[[ecowatch|ecowatch]]|archive-date=2015-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222122011/https://ecowatch.com/2015/12/17/elon-musk-solar/}}</ref> 和[[太空探索|太空探索]]的未来。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Hays|first=Brooks|url=http://www.upi.com/Science_News/2015/12/21/Watch-tonight-SpaceX-tries-again-for-historic-rocket-landing/2121450732799/|title=SpaceX makes history, successfully lands reusable rocket|publisher=[[United_Press_International|UPI]]|accessdate=27 December 2015|date=21 December 2015|archive-date=2015-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224230700/http://www.upi.com/Science_News/2015/12/21/Watch-tonight-SpaceX-tries-again-for-historic-rocket-landing/2121450732799/}}</ref> 2017年4月20日，厄本又在马斯克提议大约一个半月后，发表了有关马斯克的[[超人类主义|超人类主义]]人机界面公司 [[Neuralink|Neuralink]] 的深度文章。

目前网站文章在''[[赫芬顿邮报|《赫芬顿邮报》]]''<ref>{{Cite news|author=Urban|first=Tim|title=20 Things I Learned While I Was in North Korea|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/wait-but-why/visiting-north-korea_b_4256519.html|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=11 November 2013|work=[[The_Huffington_Post|The Huffington Post]]|archive-date=2017-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170920031605/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/wait-but-why/visiting-north-korea_b_4256519.html}}</ref> 和''Lifehacker'' <ref>{{Cite news|author=Urban|first=Tim|title=Taming the Mammoth: Why You Should Stop Caring What Other People Think|url=http://lifehacker.com/taming-the-mammoth-why-you-should-stop-caring-what-oth-1628033209|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=28 August 2014|publisher=[[Lifehacker|Lifehacker]]|archive-date=2022-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220222043923/https://lifehacker.com/taming-the-mammoth-why-you-should-stop-caring-what-oth-1628033209}}</ref>上同步刊出，并被其他网站引用。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Bendix|first=Aria|title=A Typical American Life, Week by Week|url=http://www.citylab.com/work/2015/08/the-life-of-a-typical-american-in-weeks/401645/|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=19 August 2015|publisher=[[CityLab_(web_magazine)|CityLab]]|archive-date=2017-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170501171814/http://www.citylab.com/work/2015/08/the-life-of-a-typical-american-in-weeks/401645/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Swanson|first=Ana|title=How so many of the world's people live in so little of its space|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2015/09/03/how-so-many-of-the-worlds-people-live-in-so-little-of-its-space/|accessdate=22 December 2015|date=3 September 2015|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|archive-date=2021-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210731074406/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2015/09/03/how-so-many-of-the-worlds-people-live-in-so-little-of-its-space/}}</ref>

2016年2月，厄本就拖延症发表了[[TED大会|TED演讲]]。该演讲曾是TED演讲中最快获得1000万观看次数的影片，也是TED主讲台演讲中观看次数第二高的。<ref name="talk">{{Cite web|title=Inside the mind of a master procrastinator|url=http://www.ted.com/talks/tim_urban_inside_the_mind_of_a_master_procrastinator|accessdate=8 June 2016|author=Urban|first=Tim|publisher=[[TED_(conferences)|TED]]|archive-date=2022-05-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220515173203/https://www.ted.com/talks/tim_urban_inside_the_mind_of_a_master_procrastinator}}</ref>

== 创作者背景 ==
蒂姆·厄本（与歌手/演员蒂姆·厄本（ Tim Urban ）不是同一人）出生于1981年，在马萨诸塞州牛顿长大。<ref name="WaitButWhy.com">{{Cite web|title=It’s 2020 and you’re in the future|url=https://waitbutwhy.com/2020/01/its-2020-and-youre-in-the-future.html|accessdate=3 October 2020|author=Urban|first=Tim|publisher=[[waitbutwhy.com|waitbutwhy.com]]|archive-date=2022-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517025450/https://waitbutwhy.com/2020/01/its-2020-and-youre-in-the-future.html}}</ref><ref name="Underneath the Turban">{{Cite web|title=Underneath the Turban|url=http://timurban.blogspot.com/|accessdate=3 October 2020|publisher=[[blogspot|blogspot]]|archive-date=2021-05-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515014343/https://timurban.blogspot.com/}}</ref> 他以出色的成绩从哈佛大学政府学专业毕业，获得文学学士。他曾从事教辅工作，辅导几乎所有的科目，帮助学生准备SAT考试，SAT学科测试，ACT，GRE和ISEE测试。<ref name="Tim Urban on crunchbase.com">{{Cite web|title=Tim Urban on Crunchbase.com|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/person/tim-urban|accessdate=3 October 2020|publisher=[[crunchbase.com|crunchbase.com]]|archive-date=2022-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220513160000/https://www.crunchbase.com/person/tim-urban}}</ref> 建立 Wait But Why 之前，厄本在Blogspot上写博客，博客名为“头巾之下”（Turban有头巾的意思，也是厄本名字T. Urban的组合。）。 

安德鲁·芬恩以优异的成绩毕业于密歇根大学罗斯商学院，并偶尔在UCLA安德森商学院担任演讲嘉宾。<ref name="Andrew Finn on crunchbase.com">{{Cite web|title=Andrew Finn on Crunchbase.com|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/person/andrew-finn|accessdate=3 October 2020|publisher=[[crunchbase.com|crunchbase.com]]|archive-date=2013-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110145732/http://www.crunchbase.com/person/andrew-finn}}</ref>

Wait But Why 并不是厄本和芬恩的第一次合作。2007年，他们开发了一个名为ArborBridge的项目，其目的是为学生准备美国大学录取并帮助他们取得更高的成绩。<ref name="Tim Urban on crunchbase.com">{{Cite web|title=Tim Urban on Crunchbase.com|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/person/tim-urban|accessdate=3 October 2020|publisher=[[crunchbase.com|crunchbase.com]]}}</ref>

